msgid "How to Style Your IPT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:4
msgid ""
"For simple customization in versions 2.6 or higher please use xref:"
"administration.adoc[UI Management]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Customization using `custom.css` does not work in version 2.5.0, see https://"
"github.com/gbif/ipt/issues/1634[this issue]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Basic customizations can be made by editing `$tomcat/webapps/ipt/styles/main."
"css`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Styling an IPT requires deployment using a servlet container like Tomcat.  A "
"deployment from Linux packages or Docker could only be styled by overriding "
"the `custom.css` file in a forward proxy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:17
msgid ""
"The following guide explains how to customize the IPT, and preserve your "
"customization when upgrading your IPT's version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:19
msgid "In short, customization can be achieved by applying CSS overrides."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Apply your desired CSS overrides in `custom.css` (choose a different colour "
"scheme for example). You can find this file inside the deployed WAR folder, "
"e.g. `$tomcat/webapps/ipt/styles`. The original https://github.com/gbif/ipt/"
"blob/master/src/main/webapp/styles/custom.css[custom.css] comes pre-"
"populated with a set of example CSS overrides to change the colours used in "
"buttons, links, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Upon completion, backup the `custom.css` file somewhere safe so that it can "
"be added once again after each IPT upgrade, which unfortunately will "
"overwrite the `custom.css` file each time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/customization.adoc:24
msgid ""
"Take a look at the screenshot to see the effect of changing the default CSS."
msgstr ""

